        "definition": "R5: `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]`",
        "comment": "Element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` is part of an existing definition because parent element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem` requires an extension for additional cardinality.\nElement `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` as `SourceIsBroaderThanTarget`.\nThe standard extension `alternate-reference` has been mapped as the representation of FHIR R5 element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` with unmapped reference targets: BiologicallyDerivedProduct, InventoryItem, NutritionProduct.\nSource element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` has unmapped reference types. While the target element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` is a choice type and does not allow extensions, the `alternate-reference` extension can be applied to Reference values within it.",
